// Page HeroOrVigilante Text :
"P2189036437" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>You're a Cruel One, Mr. Phipps</color></span></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span></scale><br><br>An alarm rings on your police communicator. Activating it, you find out that Arachnos has kidnapped the man known as Westin Phipps and are currently airing their interrogation of the man. You push a few buttons to bring up the video feed of the interrogation...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>The Arachnos soldier in the video violently backhands Phipps, demanding that he tell them everything about the up and coming heroes within the Rogue Isles. Phipps refuses, stating that he would never 'betray the people that are so dear to him'. He is hit again, though he refuses to talk.<br><br>You know better, however - Westin Phipps is a tool for Arachnos. Investigating further, you discover that Arachnos is broadcasting this to draw attention away from the kidnapping of several prominent figures in the Isles - one being the reporter, Amanda Vines.</color></scale></font><br><br>You weren't sure how low Arachnos could possibly stoop, though the heartless Westin Phipps shows just how cutthroat they are. If Arachnos thinks they can use this act to distract everyone else from these kidnappings, they have another thing coming to them. Someone needs to rescue Amanda Vines and the other people in the Isles who <i>truthfully</i> stand for the people.<br><br>Westin Phipps, however, just might be the most evil man you've ever heard of, purposefully earning the trust of the people in the Isles, only to betray them. Just the thought of what he does is utterly disgusting. He is a man who has never <i>truly</i> paid for his crimes against his fellow man. It's time for that to change - <i>today</i>."
// Answer Text :
"P3082079169" "HERO: Save the true heroes of the Isles!"
// Answer Text :
"P1019759678" "VIGILANTE: Pummel Westin Phipps into a pulp!"
// Page Rogue Text :
"P32836797" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>You're a Cruel One, Mr. Phipps</color></span></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span></scale><br><br>An alarm rings on your police communicator. Activating it, you find out that Arachnos has kidnapped the man known as Westin Phipps and are currently airing their interrogation of the man. You push a few buttons to bring up the video feed of the interrogation...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>The Arachnos soldier in the video violently backhands Phipps, demanding that he tell them everything about the up and coming heroes within the Rogue Isles. Phipps refuses, stating that he would never 'betray the people that are so dear to him'. He is hit again, though he refuses to talk.<br><br>You know better, however - Westin Phipps is a tool for Arachnos. Investigating further, you discover that Arachnos is broadcasting this to draw attention away from the kidnapping of several prominent figures in the Isles - one being the reporter, Amanda Vines.</color></scale></font><br><br>You know all too well the dance that Arachnos is doing with Westin Phipps. He's nothing but a heartless con artist who is so deep in the pockets of Arachnos that he can't even see the light. Unfortunately, everyone seems fooled by this little scam he's running with Arachnos, meaning the organization is getting away with the kidnappings of these people in the Isles. Someone needs to do something, or else Arachnos and Phipps will get away with yet another travesty in the Isles - all while Phipps becomes a hero for the poor in the slums."
// Answer Text :
"P2416246576" "HERO: Save the heroes of the Rogue Isles!"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
